oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: General Cheatham
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Portrait photograph of General Benjamin Franklin "Frank" Cheatham (October 20, 1820- September 4, 1886). Cheatham was a Tennessee planter, California gold miner, and a general in the Confederate States Army during the American Civil War.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Portrait photographs; Veterans
